          "correct": "b",
          "difficulty": "hard",
          "explanation": "Given \\(a^{\\frac{m}{n}} = b\\), then \\(a^{-\\frac{m}{n}} = \\frac{1}{b}\\).\nSo \\(a^{-\\frac{m}{n}} + a^{\\frac{m}{n}} = \\frac{1}{b} + b = b + \\frac{1}{b}\\)."
        },
        {
          "id": "icse_9_ch07_C_005",
          "text": "Find the value of \\(x\\) if \\(\\left(\\frac{2^{x+1} \\times 4^{x-1}}{8^{2x-3}}\\right) = 2^{5}\\).",
          "options": {
            "a": "3",
            "b": "4",
            "c": "2",
            "d": "1"
          },
          "correct": "a",
          "difficulty": "hard",
          "explanation": "Express all in base 2:\n\\(4^{x-1} = (2^2)^{x-1} = 2^{2x - 2}\\)\n\\(8^{2x -3} = (2^3)^{2x -3} = 2^{6x - 9}\\)\nSo numerator:\n\\(2^{x+1} \\times 2^{2x - 2} = 2^{x+1 + 2x - 2} = 2^{3x -1}\\)\nDenominator:\n\\(2^{6x - 9}\\)\nExpression:\n\\(\\frac{2^{3x -1}}{2^{6x - 9}} = 2^{3x -1 - (6x - 9)} = 2^{3x -1 - 6x + 9} = 2^{-3x + 8}\\)\nGiven equal to \\(2^{5}\\), so:\n\\(-3x + 8 = 5 \\Rightarrow -3x = -3 \\Rightarrow x = 1\\)\nCorrect answer is 1 (option d)."
